sql:
SELECT start_time, end_time, performance_data
FROM rendering_logs
WHERE log_id = 0;

SELECT scene_id, COUNT(object_id) AS object_count
FROM scene_objects
GROUP BY scene_id;

SELECT AVG(strftime('%s', rl.end_time) - strftime('%s', rl.start_time)) AS average_rendering_time
FROM rendering_logs rl
WHERE rl.object_count > 5 AND rl.material_count > 3;

SELECT COUNT(object_id) AS object_count
FROM scene_objects
WHERE scene_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Average rendering time is a key performance metric for rendering processes; 
- Rendering scenes with complex materials, objects, and lighting configurations typically takes longer; 
- Rendering time can be influenced by factors such as hardware, software, and scene complexity.
